  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is utilizing ultrasound measurement to measure neuromuscular disease status in
      adult patients. The hypothesis is the by quantifying ultrasound data, it is possible that
      ultrasound can be utilized as a tool to determine if a disease is responding to therapy or
      progressing.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
