  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Quantitative ultrasound data, including quantified grayscale data and backscattered acoustic data</measure>
    <time_frame>1 year</time_frame>
    <description>Ultrasound data will be collected on multiple muscles in each person. The images will then be quantified using either 1. A grayscale technique in which the images themselves are analyzed via standard image software (e.g., Adobe Photoshop) as to level of echo intensity in a pre-specific region of interest or 2. the raw quantified backscatter data is captured by the transducer, expressed as a unit of power, in the same pre-specified area of interest</description>
  </primary_outcome>
